cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.SE 

This paper deals with probabilistic reasoning and modeling using influence diagrams, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on sensitivity analysis and updating algorithms also suggests a strong connection to systems and control theory (cs.SI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the use of equivalence classes and decision thresholds suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE) and formal methods.
